WEBVTT

00:01.034 --> 00:02.101
♪

00:02.103 --> 00:03.035
[knock knock]

00:04.504 --> 00:06.305
Hey Spike. What's up?

00:06.307 --> 00:08.073
Just, uh, wanted to
make sure you're ready

00:08.075 --> 00:09.641
for your big
ceremony today.

00:09.643 --> 00:13.312
Yup. Wow, I still can't
believe my friends and I

00:13.314 --> 00:16.248
are getting medals of honor.

00:16.250 --> 00:19.351
Are you kidding? You
totally deserve it!

00:19.353 --> 00:25.357
After all, you saved Equestria
from Queen Chrysalis

00:25.359 --> 00:29.361
with the help of Trixie
and Thorax and Discord.

00:29.363 --> 00:33.465
Uh, yeah. I know what
happened. I was kinda there?

00:33.467 --> 00:38.203
Oh, right. Uh, so
what are you wearing?

00:38.205 --> 00:41.774
Not sure. Why? Am I
supposed to dress up?

00:41.776 --> 00:45.444
No. I mean, you could. It's
like Rarity always says:

00:45.446 --> 00:49.314
"There's no such thing
as overdressed darling.

00:49.316 --> 00:51.717
You're just the best-looking
pony in the room!"

00:51.719 --> 00:53.052
[awkward laugh]

00:54.687 --> 00:56.388
What are you
looking at?

00:56.390 --> 00:57.423
No, don't look!

00:59.826 --> 01:04.630
Cuz there was a spider there
but it's gone now so...

01:04.632 --> 01:05.697
Thanks, Starlight!
Bye!

01:08.835 --> 01:10.102
[door closes]

01:11.738 --> 01:16.442
Heh heh. She had no idea.
We're a good team, Sparkle.

01:16.444 --> 01:21.580
Sparkle? [laughs] Yeah we are.
So, do you think she'll like it?

01:21.582 --> 01:25.217
I want this present to
say "I'm so proud of you,

01:25.219 --> 01:27.486
both as a mentor
and a friend.

01:27.488 --> 01:30.722
Equestria is safer
thanks to you."

01:30.724 --> 01:34.460
Oh. I thought you were getting
her a mirror, like yours.

01:34.462 --> 01:36.395
I am.

01:36.397 --> 01:37.830
Maybe you should
get her a card,

01:37.832 --> 01:39.765
cause I don't think the
mirror will say all that.

01:39.767 --> 01:41.400
But I think
she'll like it.

01:41.402 --> 01:43.335
It's just what
her room needs.

01:43.337 --> 01:45.537
The first thing she'll see
when she wakes up is herself

01:45.539 --> 01:47.506
surrounded by all her friends!

01:47.508 --> 01:49.775
I plan on giving it to
her after the ceremony.

01:49.777 --> 01:51.510
Yeah, about that.

01:51.512 --> 01:54.146
Don't you need to get the castle
ready for the celebration?

01:54.148 --> 01:56.215
Nah. Pinkie Pie's
got that covered.

01:57.283 --> 01:58.283
Hm.

02:04.824 --> 02:08.360
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

02:08.362 --> 02:10.295
<i>♪ Aaaahhh</i>

02:10.297 --> 02:12.364
<i>♪ My little Pony</i>

02:12.366 --> 02:14.766
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

02:14.768 --> 02:16.635
<i>♪ My Little Pony</i>

02:16.637 --> 02:19.238
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

02:19.240 --> 02:21.306
<i>♪ Big adventure!</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun</i>

02:21.308 --> 02:23.475
<i>♪ A beautiful heart!  ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

02:23.477 --> 02:25.611
<i>♪ Sharing kindness</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat</i>

02:25.613 --> 02:27.613
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

02:27.615 --> 02:29.748
<i>♪ To have my little pony</i>

02:29.750 --> 02:33.252
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:33.254 --> 02:34.186
♪

02:40.760 --> 02:43.896
Starlight, Trixie,
Thorax and Discord

02:43.898 --> 02:46.365
were brave in the
face of danger,

02:46.367 --> 02:48.567
resourceful when
things got challenging

02:48.569 --> 02:50.602
and proved that the
bonds of friendship,

02:50.604 --> 02:54.873
no matter how unlikely, are
stronger than any adversity.

02:54.875 --> 02:56.742
By stopping
Queen Chrysalis,

02:56.744 --> 02:58.944
not only did they
save Equestria,

02:58.946 --> 03:01.914
they set the changelings
free from her reign.

03:01.916 --> 03:06.518
Go Discord! Yahoo!

03:06.520 --> 03:08.554
[giggle]

03:08.556 --> 03:11.924
And that's why we're proud
and honored to give them

03:11.926 --> 03:15.227
the Equestrian Pink
Hearts of Courage.

03:15.229 --> 03:19.198
[cheering]

03:19.200 --> 03:26.238
♪

03:28.474 --> 03:32.711
Yeah! Oh! Not quite!

03:34.480 --> 03:38.450
All right! There it is.
YAAAAAAY!

03:38.452 --> 03:40.819
♪

03:40.821 --> 03:42.988
We are so proud of you all.

03:42.990 --> 03:46.992
[cheering]

03:49.762 --> 03:55.500
<i>♪ [dance music]</i>

03:55.502 --> 03:59.238
It was the Great and
Powerful Trixie's pleasure

03:59.240 --> 04:01.907
to save you from
your imminent doom.

04:01.909 --> 04:06.011
Yes. Because you did
it all by yourself.

04:06.013 --> 04:09.514
I can't believe you managed
to do it without magic.

04:09.516 --> 04:11.350
It was amazing!

04:11.352 --> 04:13.919
No one's ever stood up
to Chrysalis like that.

04:13.921 --> 04:18.624
Oh, I just did what
anypony would've done.

04:18.626 --> 04:20.592
It's a wonderful
feeling, isn't it?

04:20.594 --> 04:22.327
Watching your
student shine

04:22.329 --> 04:24.463
the way you always
knew they could.

04:24.465 --> 04:27.299
My cheeks are sore.

04:27.301 --> 04:30.269
I don't think I've ever
smiled this much in my life.

04:30.271 --> 04:32.838
I can only imagine
what that feels like.

04:35.541 --> 04:38.844
Yes, Starlight is student
of the year, isn't she?

04:38.846 --> 04:40.779
She has so much
potential.

04:40.781 --> 04:42.714
So, what are we going
to do with her?

04:42.716 --> 04:45.751
And by "we" I
definitely mean you.

04:45.753 --> 04:47.619
Being her mentor
and all that,

04:47.621 --> 04:51.423
her destiny falls
squarely on your haunches.

04:51.425 --> 04:52.724
[zap zap]

04:52.726 --> 04:54.493
Oh, don't you worry.

04:54.495 --> 04:55.894
I've planned enough
friendship lessons

04:55.896 --> 04:57.696
to cover the next
three years.

04:57.698 --> 05:00.399
[Laughing]

05:00.401 --> 05:01.400
What's so funny?

05:01.402 --> 05:03.035
No, no.

05:03.037 --> 05:06.071
Clearly Starlight is beyond
basic friendship lessons.

05:06.073 --> 05:09.541
She just won a medal,
for Equestria's sake!

05:09.543 --> 05:13.645
I thought you were joking.
You are joking, right?

05:13.647 --> 05:17.015
[nervous laugh]
Of course I was.

05:17.017 --> 05:20.552
Obviously you should have a
grand master plan for her,

05:20.554 --> 05:23.889
the same way Celestia
set you on a path

05:23.891 --> 05:26.858
that eventually
made you a princess.

05:26.860 --> 05:29.027
Yup.

05:29.029 --> 05:34.066
Oh, good. I'm sure she can't
wait to hear all about it!

05:37.503 --> 05:41.340
So how's the whole
ruling-a-kingdom thing going?

05:41.342 --> 05:45.577
It's a bit... overwhelming.
But we're adjusting.

05:45.579 --> 05:48.647
So you can't have friendship
without makeovers?

05:48.649 --> 05:50.649
Not exactly.

05:52.385 --> 05:54.052
Oh, Starlight!

05:54.054 --> 05:56.855
Princess Twilight has something
very important to tell us.

05:56.857 --> 06:01.426
Well, just you really, but
I'm nosey and I want to hear.

06:01.428 --> 06:03.495
OK. Would you
excuse me?

06:03.497 --> 06:05.497
[zap]

06:05.499 --> 06:06.898
Never mind.

06:06.900 --> 06:10.602
Well, Twilight was
just about to reveal

06:10.604 --> 06:13.705
her grand master
plan for you.

06:13.707 --> 06:15.674
Really? I was kind
of wondering

06:15.676 --> 06:17.075
what we were going
to do next.

06:17.077 --> 06:21.046
Yes, I'd say we were
both fairly interested.

06:21.048 --> 06:25.984
Of course you are. And I
do have a plan, obviously,

06:25.986 --> 06:28.420
but now's clearly not
the time to do it.

06:28.422 --> 06:30.422
You should enjoy your party.

06:30.424 --> 06:33.892
The Ponyville Chronicle
wants to take our picture!

06:33.894 --> 06:36.495
Ugh. You too,
Discord.

06:38.631 --> 06:39.498
[sigh]

06:39.500 --> 06:40.599
[poof]

06:40.601 --> 06:42.734
PSST. I see what you're doing.

06:42.736 --> 06:44.035
You do?

06:44.037 --> 06:46.671
You already planned
the perfect moment

06:46.673 --> 06:49.608
during the party to make
the grand announcement

06:49.610 --> 06:51.943
to everypony
about your plan!

06:53.546 --> 06:54.946
Brava, Twilight.

06:54.948 --> 06:57.082
I can't wait to tell
Fluttershy and the others!

06:57.084 --> 06:58.617
Discord, no.

07:03.556 --> 07:07.025
Twilight? Are you reading
during a party again?

07:07.027 --> 07:09.494
No, no, no. She's
already good at that.

07:09.496 --> 07:12.798
She mastered this. She
taught me about this one!

07:12.800 --> 07:15.000
Wild guess: something's wrong.

07:15.002 --> 07:17.569
Spike, I'm a terrible mentor.

07:17.571 --> 07:19.805
Why didn't I come up with
a path for Starlight?

07:19.807 --> 07:22.541
Princess Celestia had it
all figured out for me.

07:22.543 --> 07:24.142
[gasp] That's it!

07:27.847 --> 07:29.681
I had years' worth
of friendship lessons

07:29.683 --> 07:30.949
ready to go,

07:30.951 --> 07:32.717
but when we were
captured by Chrysalis,

07:32.719 --> 07:35.187
Starlight took charge
and really stepped up.

07:35.189 --> 07:36.755
I don't think
friendship lessons

07:36.757 --> 07:38.790
are enough for
her anymore.

07:38.792 --> 07:42.461
So you have an overachieving
student? Sounds familiar.

07:43.796 --> 07:45.797
That's why I had
to talk to you.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.833
You of all ponies
would know what to do.

07:47.835 --> 07:50.602
I mean, you were me
and I was Starlight.

07:50.604 --> 07:52.938
But for now, I need you to
pretend you're you and I'm me.

07:52.940 --> 07:54.473
Huh?

07:54.475 --> 07:55.874
Go on.

07:55.876 --> 07:58.109
When I was your student
and you were in this place,

07:58.111 --> 08:02.581
you... oh no. You
sent me to Ponyville.

08:02.583 --> 08:04.049
Which means, it's
time for me

08:04.051 --> 08:05.717
to send Starlight
Glimmer away!

08:09.956 --> 08:11.590
I can't believe it.

08:11.592 --> 08:14.993
It really is time for
Starlight to go, isn't it?

08:14.995 --> 08:17.829
Only you can make
that decision.

08:17.831 --> 08:21.066
It's a difficult one, but your
heart knows what's right.

08:21.068 --> 08:23.568
Even as it hurts.

08:23.570 --> 08:24.836
Where are you going
to send her?

08:26.606 --> 08:28.240
Too soon?

08:28.242 --> 08:30.709
No. This is something
I have to do.

08:34.247 --> 08:35.547
Oh, boy.

08:35.549 --> 08:37.516
Oh, boy?

08:37.518 --> 08:39.150
Whatever Twilight's
planning for Starlight

08:39.152 --> 08:41.753
is going to be
so exciting!

08:41.755 --> 08:45.090
Hm. Wonder why she didn't
tell any of us about it?

08:45.092 --> 08:48.226
Probably because you're not as
close as you think you are.

08:49.929 --> 08:53.665
Just kidding. She wanted
it to be a big surprise.

08:53.667 --> 08:55.734
Just between us,
she's getting ready

08:55.736 --> 08:58.169
to make a big
announcement!

08:58.171 --> 09:00.839
Eeeee. That's so
exciting! And surprising.

09:00.841 --> 09:02.307
Usually you tell
your party planner

09:02.309 --> 09:04.075
about all your plans
for your party.

09:04.077 --> 09:05.844
Rainbow Dash: Well, she
definitely has one.

09:05.846 --> 09:08.313
I mean when has
Twilight not had a plan?

09:10.783 --> 09:14.920
[mumbling] Hm,
gosh, I don't know.

09:14.922 --> 09:17.756
[gasp] I GOT IT! Since
defeating Chrysalis,

09:17.758 --> 09:19.224
Starlight's given
the changelings

09:19.226 --> 09:21.626
an opportunity to
revolutionize their society.

09:21.628 --> 09:23.161
Maybe I can send her there.

09:23.163 --> 09:24.629
[whoosh]

09:29.735 --> 09:31.603
Cool spell.

09:31.605 --> 09:33.271
If Starlight goes to
the changeling hive,

09:33.273 --> 09:35.941
she can help them adjust
to their new way of life.

09:35.943 --> 09:38.610
OK, friendship one-oh-one:

09:38.612 --> 09:41.613
Thorax and I are going to
show you how to compromise.

09:41.615 --> 09:45.317
I want to have honeysuckle
nectar for lunch.

09:45.319 --> 09:49.854
I would like a sandwich.
Oh, no. What should we do?

09:49.856 --> 09:52.657
Attack! The winner
gets to choose!

09:52.659 --> 09:55.627
[excited chatter]

09:55.629 --> 09:59.898
OR, Thorax and I can
talk about it and come up

09:59.900 --> 10:02.267
with a solution that
works for everypony.

10:02.269 --> 10:04.803
Starlight. How do
you feel about

10:04.805 --> 10:08.206
honeysuckle and peanut
butter sandwiches?

10:08.208 --> 10:11.209
Why, that sounds
delicious.

10:11.211 --> 10:12.911
Compromise!

10:14.747 --> 10:17.682
[chatter]

10:17.684 --> 10:19.751
Um, this doesn't
seem like something

10:19.753 --> 10:21.786
Starlight and
Thorax would do.

10:21.788 --> 10:24.089
Uh, this is Twilight's
fantasy, Spike.

10:24.091 --> 10:26.191
There is no wrong
way to fantasize.

10:26.193 --> 10:27.892
Thank you.

10:27.894 --> 10:31.963
Starlight Glimmer is a most
apt and perspicacious pony!

10:31.965 --> 10:35.066
Yep, definitely a
Twilight fantasy.

10:35.068 --> 10:37.902
This seems like a lovely
path for Starlight.

10:37.904 --> 10:39.838
The Changelings have
so much to learn

10:39.840 --> 10:42.707
about how to enjoy love
through friendships.

10:42.709 --> 10:45.343
Starlight would be busy
for a very long time,

10:45.345 --> 10:50.115
but her work there
would be very rewarding.

10:50.117 --> 10:52.884
Or dangerous. It would
only take one Changeling

10:52.886 --> 10:54.185
to deviate from the pack.

11:00.960 --> 11:02.027
[evil laugh]

11:03.429 --> 11:07.899
Hi, I'm Starlight Glimmer.
What's your name?

11:07.901 --> 11:09.834
Uh, Cornicle?

11:09.836 --> 11:14.105
PFFFT! HA! What kind
of name is that?

11:14.107 --> 11:19.444
Your wings are so
um, see-through.

11:19.446 --> 11:25.316
I'm so glad I'm a pony.
Are you like bugs or what?

11:25.318 --> 11:27.352
[smack smack smack]

11:30.690 --> 11:32.924
There she is! Get her!

11:32.926 --> 11:34.826
[angry shouts]

11:36.996 --> 11:39.898
Um, that probably
won't happen.

11:39.900 --> 11:42.434
But it could. I can't
just send her off to

11:42.436 --> 11:45.103
Celestia-knows-where without
thinking it through!

11:45.105 --> 11:47.939
Huh. I was not aware
that I was an expression.

11:47.941 --> 11:49.974
An appropriate one, of course,

11:49.976 --> 11:52.077
for even I don't
know the answer.

11:52.079 --> 11:54.379
This is a momentous
decision.

11:54.381 --> 11:57.148
You must consider all
the possibilities.

11:57.150 --> 12:02.053
Rethink, rethink, rethink...
What about the dragons?

12:02.055 --> 12:04.122
I can send Starlight
to the Dragon Lands.

12:04.124 --> 12:06.257
She and Ember would
totally hit it off!

12:06.259 --> 12:07.826
[whoosh]

12:07.828 --> 12:10.895
<i>♪ [scary music]</i>

12:10.897 --> 12:13.098
Emberrrr!

12:13.100 --> 12:14.799
Starliiiiight!

12:17.269 --> 12:19.771
You ready to do some
death-defying dragon stuff?

12:19.773 --> 12:21.873
Totally.

12:21.875 --> 12:23.508
OK, that doesn't sound anything

12:23.510 --> 12:25.810
like Ember or Starlight.

12:25.812 --> 12:27.879
Who knows what their
dynamic would be, Spike?

12:27.881 --> 12:30.348
♪

12:30.350 --> 12:34.385
[explosions]

12:37.256 --> 12:38.323
[gasp]

12:39.225 --> 12:40.759
[hollow knocks]

12:40.761 --> 12:42.360
Freaky.

12:42.362 --> 12:44.929
Starlight will love it
in the dragon lands.

12:44.931 --> 12:47.232
In her letters, Ember
said dragons do a lot

12:47.234 --> 12:50.101
of fun things: The Feast
of Fires, the Dragon Bowl,

12:50.103 --> 12:52.470
Clawchella...

12:52.472 --> 12:56.341
Starlight could be there
for a really long time.

12:56.343 --> 12:59.177
But then again, not
all dragons like ponies

12:59.179 --> 13:00.478
as much as Ember does.

13:02.081 --> 13:03.882
Hey, Twinkle Star!

13:03.884 --> 13:05.850
It's uh, Starlight Glimmer.

13:05.852 --> 13:08.253
Star-kle Light-star?

13:08.255 --> 13:10.121
Starlight Glimmer.

13:10.123 --> 13:11.556
Yeah Whatever. You
wanna hang with us?

13:13.392 --> 13:15.093
What are we diving into?

13:15.095 --> 13:16.928
Lava!

13:16.930 --> 13:17.929
WHAT?!

13:19.131 --> 13:21.099
Twilight, this is crazy!

13:21.101 --> 13:23.168
[zap]

13:23.170 --> 13:24.969
Starlight's really
good with magic.

13:24.971 --> 13:26.304
She could just stop
herself from falling

13:26.306 --> 13:28.072
into a pit of lava.

13:28.074 --> 13:30.975
What if she didn't
realize it was happening?

13:30.977 --> 13:32.844
You just never know, Spike!

13:32.846 --> 13:35.246
I just need to think of
someplace safe to send her.

13:35.248 --> 13:36.948
Some place safe, some place
safe. Some place safe.

13:38.250 --> 13:39.984
I could send her to
the Crystal Empire

13:39.986 --> 13:42.587
to continue her magical
studies with Sunburst!

13:42.589 --> 13:44.255
[zap]

13:47.126 --> 13:48.593
It'll be perfect!

13:48.595 --> 13:50.428
Sunburst's knowledge of
magic is only matched

13:50.430 --> 13:52.497
by Starlight's abilities.

13:52.499 --> 13:57.001
I've got it! Try placing your
horn directly on the potion

13:57.003 --> 13:58.970
and picture the clock
you wish to make.

14:00.406 --> 14:01.873
[zap]

14:01.875 --> 14:04.209
[cuckoo cuckoo]

14:04.211 --> 14:06.010
They could challenge
each other into becoming

14:06.012 --> 14:08.479
the most talented unicorns
Equestria's ever seen!

14:08.481 --> 14:10.582
We did it! Quick,
what's next?

14:12.151 --> 14:15.486
Of course, the study of
magic is a lifelong pursuit

14:15.488 --> 14:17.322
and Starlight could
be there for a while,

14:17.324 --> 14:18.957
especially once they
start attempting

14:18.959 --> 14:20.959
the really complicated stuff!

14:20.961 --> 14:24.028
Three... two... one...

14:24.030 --> 14:27.198
What if they become
too ambitious?

14:27.200 --> 14:29.200
I never would have thought
to combine Starswirl's

14:29.202 --> 14:31.870
apparition spell with
spatium flexibus!

14:31.872 --> 14:33.538
But what would
happen if we added

14:33.540 --> 14:36.107
Sonambula's tempus
objectus?

14:36.109 --> 14:38.209
If we do it just right,
it should allow us

14:38.211 --> 14:40.879
to materialize an object
that was lost in the past!

14:50.055 --> 14:51.422
No, don't do it.

14:55.127 --> 15:01.266
[scream]

15:01.268 --> 15:04.135
Starlight! NOOOO!

15:05.671 --> 15:07.605
Twilight! Snap out of it!

15:10.609 --> 15:13.211
Easy, Twilight.
It didn't happen.

15:13.213 --> 15:15.346
But it could.

15:15.348 --> 15:18.016
I just don't think I
can send her anywhere.

15:18.018 --> 15:19.684
What am I going to do?

15:19.686 --> 15:25.456
[hysterical laughter]

15:25.458 --> 15:26.991
Are you laughing at me?

15:30.229 --> 15:33.298
[hysterical laughter]

15:33.300 --> 15:36.167
I can't believe
you're laughing at me.

15:36.169 --> 15:39.370
Oh, Twilight, I'm not.
I'm laughing because

15:39.372 --> 15:41.606
I had the exact same
fears you're having.

15:41.608 --> 15:43.041
What?

15:43.043 --> 15:45.276
Let me tell you a story.

15:45.278 --> 15:49.447
Once upon a time there was
a very bright young filly.

15:49.449 --> 15:52.283
She was truly one
of my best students.

15:52.285 --> 15:54.519
Are you talking about Twilight?

15:54.521 --> 15:56.120
I can't see what
you're thinking about.

15:56.122 --> 15:58.222
Yes, Spike.

15:58.224 --> 16:04.996
♪

16:04.998 --> 16:07.398
I was constantly
surprised and impressed

16:07.400 --> 16:09.033
with her discoveries.

16:09.035 --> 16:12.270
♪

16:12.272 --> 16:14.973
But I noticed that her
pursuit of academia

16:14.975 --> 16:17.575
was preventing her from
reaching her full potential.

16:17.577 --> 16:20.244
You mean it was keeping
her isolated and alone?

16:20.246 --> 16:22.280
Uh. Yes, Spike.

16:22.282 --> 16:26.317
I had a decision to
make. But it wasn't easy.

16:28.487 --> 16:30.488
Maybe I could close the library

16:30.490 --> 16:33.124
or throw a party in the castle?

16:33.126 --> 16:35.393
She'd have to talk to
the other fillies then.

16:35.395 --> 16:39.063
♪

16:39.065 --> 16:42.433
I must send her away!

16:42.435 --> 16:46.304
I knew there was a special
group of fillies in Ponyville,

16:46.306 --> 16:48.573
but I kept inventing
all kinds of reasons

16:48.575 --> 16:51.275
why I shouldn't send you.

16:51.277 --> 16:54.145
What if she runs into a
manticore? Or what if

16:54.147 --> 16:57.181
she gets pulled into
Tartarus? Or worst of all,

16:57.183 --> 17:00.018
what if she doesn't
get along with anypony?

17:00.020 --> 17:01.352
Are we supposed
to say something?

17:01.354 --> 17:03.354
I don't think so.

17:03.356 --> 17:08.459
I kept you in Canterlot
longer than I should have.

17:08.461 --> 17:11.562
Eventually, I realized
all the anxiety I felt

17:11.564 --> 17:13.731
was because I didn't
want you to go.

17:13.733 --> 17:15.700
Really?

17:15.702 --> 17:18.403
I loved having you
as a student.

17:18.405 --> 17:20.605
You challenged me and
taught me just as much

17:20.607 --> 17:22.573
as I taught you.

17:22.575 --> 17:25.610
I am embarrassed to admit
it, but I was afraid

17:25.612 --> 17:28.746
if you made friends, you
wouldn't need me anymore.

17:30.616 --> 17:33.751
Princess Celestia,
that is so not true.

17:33.753 --> 17:36.087
I will always need you.

17:36.089 --> 17:38.489
I think Starlight Glimmer
might feel the same way

17:38.491 --> 17:41.259
about you, if that is
what you're afraid of.

17:41.261 --> 17:43.394
Maybe it is.
Just a little.

17:43.396 --> 17:47.498
Oh, it definitely
is. Like a lot.

17:47.500 --> 17:51.235
Here we are after all
these years, Twilight.

17:51.237 --> 17:53.504
We are living proof
that letting someone

17:53.506 --> 17:56.307
spread their wings doesn't
mean you no longer have

17:56.309 --> 17:58.342
a place in their lives.

17:58.344 --> 17:59.510
Thank you.

17:59.512 --> 18:01.345
And if you're still worried,

18:01.347 --> 18:03.114
you can always make
her write you letters!

18:04.149 --> 18:05.483
[giggle]

18:05.485 --> 18:08.152
[laughter]

18:13.158 --> 18:15.626
I may have let it slip
that you'd be unveiling

18:15.628 --> 18:19.263
your big plan for Starlight
tonight. Silly me.

18:19.265 --> 18:22.133
But we're all very excited to
hear what you've cooked up.

18:26.438 --> 18:30.508
You weren't coming up with
a plan just now, were you?

18:30.510 --> 18:35.313
Oh, dear. This could be
pretty embarrassing for you.

18:35.315 --> 18:37.348
Gee, thanks Discord.

18:37.350 --> 18:40.118
Anytime. I really do
love being helpful.

18:40.120 --> 18:41.385
[zap]

18:42.521 --> 18:44.122
[clink clink clink]

18:44.124 --> 18:46.324
If I could have
everypony's attention.

18:46.326 --> 18:49.260
As you all know, Starlight
Glimmer has been my pupil

18:49.262 --> 18:52.230
for a while now and I'd
hoped she'd be my pupil

18:52.232 --> 18:55.366
for a long time yet to
come, but it turns out

18:55.368 --> 18:57.201
that's just not meant to be.

18:57.203 --> 18:58.836
[gasp]

18:58.838 --> 19:02.140
Starlight, you have proved
yourself to be a kind,

19:02.142 --> 19:06.711
loyal, strong, honest
and truly magical friend.

19:06.713 --> 19:08.412
Just looking around
this room at

19:08.414 --> 19:09.881
all the new friendships
you've made,

19:09.883 --> 19:13.317
I know there's nothing
more I need to teach you.

19:13.319 --> 19:15.686
So we have a second
reason to celebrate today.

19:15.688 --> 19:17.522
Three cheers for
Starlight Glimmer

19:17.524 --> 19:19.323
on her "graduation" day!

19:19.325 --> 19:21.659
[cheers]

19:21.661 --> 19:25.563
EEE WHAT A GREAT SURPRISE!!

19:25.565 --> 19:27.532
Your future is in
your own hooves now.

19:27.534 --> 19:30.635
Wow. I was not expecting this.

19:33.205 --> 19:35.740
Darn it. I was hoping you'd
send her to my realm.

19:35.742 --> 19:37.341
We could have been roomies!

19:37.343 --> 19:40.511
Way to not pick up what
I was putting down.

19:40.513 --> 19:44.448
How do you wanna celebrate?
Girls trip to Las Pegasus?

19:44.450 --> 19:47.318
We can throw you a
changeling Gorbfest!

19:47.320 --> 19:48.819
Uh, it's more fun
than it sounds.

19:51.290 --> 19:53.891
Or we could go cause
a little mischief.

19:53.893 --> 19:58.496
I know a trick that'll turn
Celestia's castle into cheese.

19:58.498 --> 20:02.233
Do you think it's
a gouda idea? Ha!

20:02.235 --> 20:03.834
That's just the first
of many cheese jokes

20:03.836 --> 20:05.903
if we go down this path.

20:05.905 --> 20:09.607
That all sounds
wonderful but um...

20:09.609 --> 20:10.942
Give me a minute, would ya?

20:13.512 --> 20:15.279
Congratulations!

20:15.281 --> 20:16.647
Thanks!

20:16.649 --> 20:18.683
So, how do you feel?

20:18.685 --> 20:21.752
Happy, surprised, overwhelmed...

20:21.754 --> 20:25.389
I mean, not that I'm not
grateful but are you sure?

20:25.391 --> 20:28.826
♪

20:28.828 --> 20:31.462
Believe me, I've thought
long and hard about this.

20:31.464 --> 20:33.231
Of course you did.

20:33.233 --> 20:36.300
Starlight, trust
me. You're ready.

20:36.302 --> 20:37.335
Yeah.

20:38.937 --> 20:40.371
No, I'm not.

20:40.373 --> 20:41.806
What are you
talking about?

20:41.808 --> 20:43.908
I'm not ready to leave!

20:43.910 --> 20:46.444
Oh, good! Cuz I'm not
ready for that either!

20:46.446 --> 20:48.312
Here. I got you
this present.

20:51.784 --> 20:54.619
'congrats on getting a
medal of honor present',

20:54.621 --> 20:55.886
but then I was afraid
it would have to be a

20:55.888 --> 20:59.790
'I couldn't be happier
you're staying' present!

20:59.792 --> 21:03.461
It fits perfectly over your
dresser. I know. I measured!

21:03.463 --> 21:05.429
Thank you.

21:05.431 --> 21:07.665
I may not know what
comes next for you,

21:07.667 --> 21:11.702
but whatever it is, I promise
I'll always be there for you.

21:11.704 --> 21:15.306
Ohhh!

21:15.308 --> 21:18.743
[happy chatter]

21:30.856 --> 21:32.723
<u>captions by</u>
<u>sassonique</u>
- <u>Phew!</u>
